  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the duck legs</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 190°C/ 170°C (fan)/ 375°F/ Gas 5 and boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>duck legs</strong> to a baking tray and season all over with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20-25 minutes, or until you reach step 3.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Par-boil the potatoes</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> (chop any large potatoes in half).</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 minutes or until fork-tender.</p>\n<p>Once the potatoes are done, drain and leave them to steam dry for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Tip: <span class=\"text-highlight\">For</span> extra crispy potatoes, shake them around in a colander to fluff up the edges a little before roasting!</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the potatoes</strong> </p>\n<p>Once the potatoes are done, remove the <strong>duck legs</strong> from the oven. </p>\n<p>Add the<strong> drained potatoes </strong>with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up until coated in all of the duck fat (add a little vegetable oil if they're looking a little dry!).</p>\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for 50 minutes further, or until the duck is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are golden and crispy.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1707.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the cauliflower </strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>cauliflower</strong> into florets. </p>\n<p>Add the<strong> cauliflower florets</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15-20 minutes or until tender and golden.</p>",
