      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make the redcurrant jus</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Knorr</strong></span> <strong>chicken stock cube </strong>(save the rest for later!) and the <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> to a pot and bring to the boil over a high heat.</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10-15 minutes or until the sauce has reduced by half. </p>\n<p>Once reduced, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes further or until thick and glossy – this is your <strong>redcurrant jus</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>",
